dsDescriptionValue.value: These data describe the geographic relationships of the   103rd congressional districts to selected governmental and statistical   geographic entities for the entire United States, American Samoa, Guam,   Puerto Rico, and the Virgin Islands. Each record represents a census   geographic tabulation unit (GTUB), a unique combination of geographic   codes expressing specific geographic relationships. This file provides   the following information: state, congressional district, county and   county subdivision, place, American Indian/Alaska Native area,   urbanized area, urban/rural descriptor, and Metropolitan Statistical  Area/Primary Metropolitan Statistical Area (MSA/PMSA).
